    "The process begins by separating the plant from the grain, leaving behind the pods, which are typically considered waste.",
    "Currently, this waste is often burned, with the resulting ash being disposed of in landfills, which poses environmental risks.",
    "However, a more sustainable solution can be found by integrating this agricultural waste into concrete.",
    "This approach not only addresses waste management issues but also reduces the environmental impact of traditional disposal methods.",
    "By using GGPA in concrete, the harmful effects of agricultural waste on the environment can be minimized, turning a waste product into a valuable resource for the construction industry [29].Discover Civil Engineering (2024) 1:145 | https://doi.org/10.1007/s44290-024-00154-z Review BentoniteBentonite, an alumina-siliceous material, is a key component of plastic clays, with earth minerals primarily montmorillonite making up about 87% of its structure."
